{"word":"ἐξαμαρτάνω","slug":"ἐξαμαρτάνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξαμαρτάνω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσομαι</el>) (aor2 <el>-ήμαρτον</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to err from the mark, fail</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: <i>to miss one's aim</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to err, do wrong, sin</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>ἐξ. τι</el> <i>to commit</i> a fault, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be mismanaged</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}